infoparam.name: UML Note
infoparam.value:
Specification (from Prof. Vingerhoeds) - April 2019
An unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) can autonomously take off, fly in a stabilized way, and land at its destination or whenever a critical situation is encountered. It takes pictures at given locations.
Only the software related to taking pictures is modeled in this case study: the taking off, flying and landing actions are not modeled.
Pictures can be taken only when the drone is flying.
A remote system located in a ground station can send picture order to the drone.
A picture order contains the GPS position of the picture to be taken.
To know its current position, a drone has an integrated GPS.
When a picture GPS point is reached, with regards to a given threshold, the picture is taken, and then stored on a CompactFlash removable storage system.
The system needs 2 seconds to take a picture, and between 4 and 5 seconds to store it in on the memory card.
Pictures may be remotely downloaded from the ground station using a download order.
Pictures can also be read from the CompactFlash once the drone has come back from its mission.
For the sake of simplicity, in the case study, the initialization, shutdown and maintenance procedure associated with the UAV are not addressed.

textline.data: Flying is required to take pictures.
Take off and landing will not be modeled.
The model does not describe the shutdown procedure.
The model does not describe the set up procedure.
The system is supposed to be correctly initialized.
The model does not address maintenance.
None of the devices connected to the system will ever fail.
The Hw and SW components of the system will never fail.
The model does not address battery management.
The capacity of the Compact Flash memory is unlimited.
We first assume a perfect flight thanks to the absence of turbulence
The drone can encounter turbulence. The autopilot can
automatically adapt its flight orders as long as
the turbulence remains under a given threshold

thanks to the absence of turbulence
The UAV will eventually get the GPS position.

Pictures will be taken during day time.
The system shall manage memory overflow
